HUDSON FLYER broke out and bumped rival at the start, settled off pace and on the rail, continued to save ground on the turn and lacked bid. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROUGH RIDE vied for lead three wide on the backstretch, continued three wide on the turn, managed to clear rivals midway through the turn, entered lane clear and just barely held off closing inside rival at the wire. MACHO SAM vied for lead along the rail in a three pronged duel, continued along the on the turn, lost ground to leader entering the lane, responded well and gained on leader to wire to just barely miss. SOUL PRODIGY chased trio off the rail on the backstretch, continued chasing the dueling trio on the turn, launched bid three wide and failed to gain, managed to just save third at the wire. JAY BOY off bit slow and stalked the pace along the rail, continued to along the inside on the turn, roused late on the turn and made progress, split foes approaching the final sixteenth and continued to gain and just missed third. EDINBURGH EXPRESS vied between in a three pronged duel on the backstretch, continued in the tough in between position on the turn, and began to weaken entering the lane after a tough trip. OLYMPIC SILVER found a good spot tracking a three horse duel while saving ground, continued to save ground on the turn and into the lane, but failed to take advantage of good trip and weakened in the final sixteenth. HOLYJAZZ reared and came away very slow, settled well off the pace on the backstretch and mildly ridden along late to finish with mild interest. MINDSHARE hit gate and ducked out at the start, stalked pace off the rail on the backstretch and on the turn, and failed to respond when asked in the lane. JOCKEY OBJECTION, RIDER OF MACHO SAM CLAIMED INETREFERRENCE BY ROUGH RIDE ON THE TURN, AFTER REVIEW THE CLAIM WAS DISALLOWED
